Job Description:
Building the space between proven and possible, MDA Space (TSX:MDA) is a trusted mission partner to the global space industry. A robotics, satellite systems and geointelligence pioneer with a 55-year+ story of world firsts and more than 450 missions, MDA Space is a global leader in communications satellites, Earth and space observation, and space exploration and infrastructure. The MDA Space team of more than 3,000 space experts in Canada, the US and the UK has the knowledge and know-how to turn an audacious customer vision into an achievable mission – bringing to bear a one-of-a-kind mix of experience, engineering excellence and wide-eyed wonder that’s been in our DNA since day one. For those who dream big and push boundaries on the ground and in the stars to change the world for the better, we’ll take you there.

Are you ready to launch the next stage of your career in the new space economy? We would love to hear from you!

The Position

We are on the hunt for a Senior Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) Processor Analyst at our Richmond, BC, Canada office, to be a part of the next generation of Earth Observations space missions.

From detecting changes in fragile ecosystems to monitoring northern ice floes and shipping routes, our near-real time Earth observation data makes our Geointelligence team a leader in geospatial imagery, ground stations, enterprise geospatial systems and defence programs. You will join our remote sensing team that has 30+ years of experience delivering commercial and government projects such as RADARSAT-2, RapidEye, Sapphire, CASSIOPE, RADARSAT Constellation Mission and now the CHORUS Constellation of SAR satellites.

Role

This is a role suited for an ambitious professional wanting to solve complex problems and develop novel algorithms that contribute to the betterment of our world. You will contribute to our world leading Synthetic Aperture Radar processors by developing novel signal processing algorithms that generate high value imagery and real-time actionable intelligence for our customers.

Responsibilities

As a Senior Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) Processor Analyst, you may have a wide range of responsibilities that include:

Develop novel signal processing algorithms to push the boundaries of SAR performance (resolution, swath width, Moving Target Indication (MTI) and more);
Design, develop, maintain and enhance high quality SAR processor models and prototypes using current best practices in architecture and software development;
Participate in trade-off studies and find solutions to ensure algorithms are implementable on real hardware (processor and radar HW);
Investigate, troubleshoot, determine root causes and mitigate signal processing errors or induced artefacts in SAR image products;
Performs system level analyses and develops models to predict and test system performance;
Develops solutions to improve image quality;
Develops and executes calibration plans for SAR missions;
Coordinates SAR processing requirements and development with other stakeholders (payload team, applications, business development);
Generates clear and thorough written reports documenting complex algorithms and technical performance; and
Mentoring and coaching of junior team members.

Required Experience:

Undergraduate degree or higher in Electrical Engineering, Engineering Physics, Math, Physics, or a combination of related education and experience;
8 years of experience working in an engineering or technical environment or 4 years with a relevant post graduate degree ;
6 or more years working on complex signal processing systems (e.g. Radar, Medical Imaging, Sonar, etc);
Solid understanding of the principles and practices concerning the design of high speed and high throughput data analysis and transmission;
Ability and knowledge to work with MATLAB, Python or C++;
Self-starter with the ability to perform in a dynamic working environment;
Possess excellent problem solving skills;
Excellent interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills to explain concepts to wide-ranging audiences (e.g. technical team, sales team, executives, customers, etc); and
The ability to work within a large organization and understand dependencies and stakeholder needs.

Desired Experience:

A post-graduate degree in a field involving complex signal processing;
Appreciation of SAR remote sensing, including system design, operation, applications/exploitation and calibration;
Appreciation for satellite based SAR Payload design and operations;
Appreciation and understanding of modern software development methodologies;
Experience in different types of engineering life cycles as applicable from large complex programs to software development;
Appreciation for algorithm implementation on FPGA;
Ability to learn new technologies and space borne remote sensing domain knowledge quickly; and
A strong understanding of geospatial data.

